Week 1 — Paper Analysis & Data Engine
Completed
Analysed the ICCV 2025 paper; mapped the two-stage design and labelled each part as Paper-Specified / Inferred / Assumption.
Re-implemented the full InstanceDepth architecture in PyTorch from the paper alone (DINOv2 + DPT backbone, depth-range decoder, instance head, occlusion-refinement module).
Built the SAM3 annotation pipeline to convert raw RGB-D video into GID-style data: masks, tracking IDs, ground masks, depth layers.
In Progress
Generating and validating annotations across all 10 batches.
Result
Complete modular, config-driven codebase reproducing the framework.
Custom dataset built: 306 videos, 50,323 frames, 245 train / 61 test (20% split), 1 class.
Week 2 — Dataset Validation & Phase 1 Training
Completed
Validated dataset integrity; chose 504×896 input and 1 m depth bins with justification.
Trained Phase 1 (Holistic Depth Init): 55k iters, lr 1e-5, converged (loss 8.7 → 0.7).
Resolved data/training issues: invalid-depth handling, memory-safe loading, offline weights on the cluster.
In Progress
Depth-validity analysis (~19% of instances are far/small people without sensor depth — excluded from depth loss, kept for mask/class/tracking).
Result
Phase-1 baseline on test set: RMS 0.4236, REL 0.0749, RMSLOG 0.1142, LOG10 0.0316.
Week 3 — Phase 2 & 3 Training, Evaluation
Completed
Trained Phase 2 (instance head): 25k iters, encoder frozen; hardened loss + training loop for numerical stability.
Trained Phase 3 (occlusion refinement): 25k iters, lr 1e-6; verified occlusion path active (pairs detected, refinement losses nonzero).
Ran stage-wise evaluation (+H, +H+I, +H+I+R) on the test set.
In Progress
Adding instance-level / occlusion-region metrics; preparing final report and slides.
Result
Full three-phase pipeline trained end-to-end with all checkpoints saved.
Framework reproduced on custom data; dense baseline established, instance-level evaluation underway to show the occlusion-handling gain.
